snippet.textDisplay:
Thank You OAFF/Burrah/Saveraa/Jasleen for ending a near decadal drought of some seriously good music in our country.
I hope that some even better work could've been done on the lyrics side though. Not that lyrics is bad, but could've been even better and could've walked hand to hand with music even synergistically. But that's only my constructive criticism.
In the end - certainly 99.9999 out of 100.
